-- Hopewell Holdings' unit wins auction for HK$233 mln site in HK, beats estimates 
-- 
-- Wed Jun 04, 2014 05:16AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, June 4 (Reuters) - A unit of Hong Kong developer Hopewell Holdings Ltd <0054.HK> won an auction for a residential site worth HK$233 million ($30 million), the government said on Wednesday.

Hopewell outbid nine other Hong Kong developers, including Sino Land Company Ltd <0083.HK> and Emperor International Holdings Ltd <0163.HK>, to build residential developments at the site in Wan Chai district on Hong Kong Island. Two analysts gave a forecast of HK$174 million for the site of 0.03 hectares.